<% content_for :title, "Terms of Booking — Help" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Help", path: help_path },
      { label: "Terms of Booking", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Terms of Booking</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">What you agree to when completing a booking, and how the agreement system works.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Accepting the Agreement</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Before completing any booking, you're shown the current Studio Agreement and must check a
            box confirming you've read and accepted it. This is required — you can't proceed to payment
            without it.
          </p>
          <p>
            The agreement covers studio rules, conduct expectations, liability, and payment policies.
            It's written in plain language, not legal jargon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Your Agreement is Locked to Your Booking</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
          <p>
            Each booking records the exact version of the terms you agreed to at the time of payment.
            If the studio updates their agreement after your booking, your past booking is unaffected —
            you agreed to the version that was current when you paid.
          </p>
          <p>
            Future bookings will present the latest version of the agreement for you to review and accept.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Questions About the Terms</h2>
        <div class="mt-3">
          <p>
            If you have questions about the studio's terms before booking, reach out to the studio
            directly. The studio contact information is available on the home page.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
